Sharp-shinned

One of the more fascinating hawks in our area of Minnesota is the Sharp-skinned hawk.  It is not much larger than an American Robin and is the smallest hawk we have in both the US and Canada.  Good chance this one will be in Central America in a month or two #Hawks https://t.co/C8zJ9stpgv
